s_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "L2pB1", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.7168195843696594, "span": {"begin": 386, "end": 391}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "antigen-presenting cells", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.5040709376335144, "span": {"begin": 409, "end": 433}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "L2pB1 cells", "obj": "cell_line", "prob": 0.9422168135643005, "span": {"begin": 473, "end": 484}}, {"id": ["mesh:D008180", "mim:152700"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "lupus", "obj": "disease", "prob": 0.991956353187561, "span": {"begin": 488, "end": 493}}, {"id": ["NCBITaxon:10095"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "mice", "obj": "species", "prob": 0.9108001589775085, "span": {"begin": 505, "end": 509}}], "text": "In a study to investigate a novel subpopulation of B-1 cells and its roles in murine lupus, anti-double-stranded DNA (anti-dsDNA) autoantibodies were preferentially secreted by a subpopulation of CD5+ B-1 cells that expressed programmed death ligand 2 (L2pB1 cells) (Xuemei Z. 2009).&nbsp; A substantial proportion of hybridoma clones generated from L2pB1 cells reacted to dsDNA.&nbsp; L2pB1 cells are potent antigen-presenting cells and a dramatic increase of circulating L2pB1 cells in lupus-prone BXSB mice correlates with elevated serum titers of anti-dsDNA antibodies (Xuemei Z. 2009).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:23:48 +0000 2026"}